# Ab aate hain Registry pe.

Tumne bola.

> Registry ka syntax samajh nahi aaya.

Very Good.

Ye normal hai.

Kyuki ye JavaScript ka feature hai.

BullMQ ka nahi.

---

# Pehle normal object dekhte hain.

```ts
const student = {
    name: "Akash",
    age: 21,
};
```

Ab.

```ts
console.log(student.name);
```

Output

```
Akash
```

Aur.

```ts
console.log(student["name"]);
```

Output.

```
Akash
```

Notice.

Dono same hain.

---

# Ab ye dekho.

```ts
const key = "name";

console.log(student[key]);
```

Output.

```
Akash
```

Kyun?

Kyuki.

```ts
student[key]
```

Ban gaya.

```ts
student["name"]
```

Aur.

```ts
student["name"]
```

Already exist karta hai.

---

# Ab registry.

```ts
const registry = {

    welcome: welcomeHandler,

    otp: otpHandler

}
```

Ye bhi ek normal object hai.

Bas.

Isme value.

String nahi.

Function hai.

---

Diagram.

```
registry

│

├── welcome

│      │

│      ▼

│  welcomeHandler()

│

├── otp

│      │

│      ▼

│ otpHandler()
```

---

Ab.

```ts
registry.welcome
```

Kya return karega?

```
welcomeHandler
```

Ab.

```ts
registry.welcome()
```

Ho gaya.

Function call.

😂

---

# Ab EMAIL_JOB.

Tumne.

```ts
EMAIL_JOB.WELCOME
```

Likha.

Uski value kya hai?

```
send-welcome-email
```

Bas.

---

To.

```ts
const registry = {

   [EMAIL_JOB.WELCOME]: welcomeHandler

}
```

Actually ban gaya.

```ts
const registry = {

    "send-welcome-email": welcomeHandler

}
```

😂😂😂

Bas.

JavaScript ne.

Square bracket dekh kar.

Pehle value nikali.

Fir object banaya.

---

# Isko bolte hain.

## Computed Property.

Example.

```ts
const key = "name";

const obj = {

    [key]: "Akash"

}
```

JavaScript.

Banayega.

```ts
{

name:"Akash"

}
```

😂😂😂

---

# Registry me.

```ts
[EMAIL_JOB.WELCOME]
```

Ban gaya.

```ts
"send-welcome-email"
```

To object.

Ban gaya.

```ts
const registry = {

"send-welcome-email": welcomeHandler,

"send-otp-email": otpHandler

}
```

Ab.

Worker.

Kya karta hai?

---

Worker.

```ts
const handler = registry[job.name];
```

Suppose.

Queue se.

Job aayi.

```
job.name

↓

send-welcome-email
```

To.

Ye line.

Ban gayi.

```ts
registry["send-welcome-email"]
```

Aur.

Output.

```
welcomeHandler
```

😂😂😂

Bas.

---

Fir.

```ts
await handler(job)
```

Ban gaya.

```ts
await welcomeHandler(job)
```

HO GAYA.

🔥🔥🔥

---

# Ek aur example.

Maan lo.

```ts
const mobile = {

iphone:100000,

samsung:90000,

oneplus:50000

}
```

User.

Input deta hai.

```ts
const phone = "iphone";
```

Ab.

```ts
console.log(mobile[phone]);
```

Output.

```
100000
```

Kyun?

Kyuki.

Ye ban gaya.

```ts
mobile["iphone"]
```

---

Registry bhi.

Exactly.

Yehi.

Hai.

Bas.

Values.

Number nahi.

Function hain.

😂

---

# Ek aur level.

Registry ko dictionary bhi bol sakte ho.

```
English

↓

Hindi
```

```
Hello

↓

Namaste
```

Waise hi.

```
Job Name

↓

Handler
```

```
send-welcome-email

↓

welcomeHandler
```

😂😂

Isliye iska naam.

Registry.

Rakha gaya.

---

# Ab tum ek kaam karo.

BullMQ bhool jao.

Ek `calculator` banao.

```ts
const calculator = {

add:add,

sub:sub,

mul:mul,

div:div

}
```

Fir.

```ts
const operation = "add";
```

Aur.

```ts
calculator[operation](10,20)
```

Output.

```
30
```

😎

Agar ye samajh aa gaya.

To Registry 100% samajh aa jayegi.

---

## Aur ek baat...

Tumne notice kiya?

**Switch-case bhi wahi kaam kar raha tha.**

```
Job Name

↓

Case

↓

Function
```

Registry bhi wahi kar rahi hai.

Bas.

Difference ye hai.

| Switch Case                 | Registry                  |
| --------------------------- | ------------------------- |
| 200 lines                   | 10 lines                  |
| Hard to maintain            | Easy                      |
| Har nayi job pe worker edit | Sirf registry me ek entry |
| Typos detect mushkil        | Constants ke saath safe   |

🔥 **Aaj tumne BullMQ se zyada JavaScript ka ek bahut powerful pattern seekha hai.**

Aur sach bataun? Ye pattern sirf BullMQ me nahi, Express, React, NestJS, Next.js, VS Code extensions, aur bahut saare production codebases me milta hai. Jab bhi tumhe **"string → function"** mapping karni ho, registry pattern ek bahut clean solution hota hai.
